name: planting with starter fertiliser or amendment, by row crop planter | planting with starter fertiliser or amendment, by row crop planter | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/29527/documentation

This dataset represents the service of planting by row crop planter, with starter fertiliser or amendment. Seed and fertiliser are not included. The dataset covers the application of seeds and starter fertiliser in the field with a tractor of 250 hp and 10771 kg coupled to an implement that weighs 16000 kg. The functional unit (FU) is one ha seeded and the operation time is 0.21 h/FU.; 40 mÂ² are occupied inside the shed. The implement can be used to fertilising besides seeding. In this case, both activities are made in the same operation.

The activity starts from the agricultural field foreseen to be processed.

The inventory takes into account the diesel fuel consumption and the amount of agricultural machinery and of the shed, which has to be attributed to the seeding operation. Also taken into consideration is the amount of emissions to the air from combustion and the emissions to soil from tyre abrasion during the work process. Seeds and fertilisers are not taken into account. Not included are dust other than from combustion. This activity ends with the transfer back to the shed and uncoupling of the implement from the tractor.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Fuel consumption and emissions per kg diesel have been extrapolated to the US, but others inputs were taken from the original values.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: The dataset is modeled for agricultural production system in US. Data Quality indicators are adjusted accordingly.
